Title: SQL Language Expressions
Description: The NOTNULL operator is used to test if an expression is not NULL. It returns true if the expression is not NULL, and false if it is NULL.
Parameters: An expression to test for non-NULL.
Returns: True if the expression is not NULL; otherwise, false.
Examples: SELECT * FROM employees WHERE manager_id IS NOT NULL; -- Finds employees with a manager ID
SELECT name FROM products WHERE price IS NOT NULL; -- Finds products with a price specified
